S, 4.0 spd, 99 con, 89 qua, 94 dur<br><br>Nonstyled damage:<br>Avg: 103.3 ( 67 hits, 72-135 ) <br>WDC: 25.08 ( 40 hits, 19-33 )<br>ROF: 13.21 ( 28 hits, 10-18 )<br>ROA: 13.42 ( 19 hits, 10-16 )<br><br>Styled Damage:<br>Avg: 144.5 ( 15 hits, 108-184 )<br>WDC: 25.67 ( 3 hits, 22-28 )<br>ROF: 12.67 ( 3 hits, 11-14 )<br>ROA: 14.14 ( 7 hits, 13-16 )<br><br><br>This shows that regardless of the styles, the damage from rain of xxx does not increase. <br>There was a 40% increase in damage, but no increase in the damage adds (within <br>statistical limits for such a small test set)<br><br><br>B and C&gt; The following shows that DPS has no effect on rain of xxx, but speed does.<br><br>storebought rowan staff, 1.4 dps, 4.5 spd, 85 qual<br>Avg: 4.7  (80 hits, 3-6)       <br>WDC: 28.6 (41 hits, 22-36)<br>ROF: 14.8 (13 hits, 11-18)<br>ROA: 15.1 (12 hits, 12-19)<br><br>storebought ironwood staff, 5.9DPS, 4.5 spd, 85% qual<br>Avg: 21.8 (38 hits, 17-26)<br>WDC: 28.8 (5 hits, 25-32)       <br>ROF: 16.1 (9 hits, 13-19)<br>ROA: 15.1 (13 hits, 12-18)<br><br>storebought short sword.   1.5 dps   2.4 spd  85 qual<br>Avg: 3.15 (108 hits, 2-4) <br>WDC: 15.46 (48 hits, 12-20)<br>ROF: 8.63 (19 hits, 6-10)<br>ROA: 7.57 (21 hits, 6-10)<br><br>As you can see, the 2 staves, of identical speeds, with varying DPS give the same damage adds.<br>However, the shortsword, with nearly the same DPS as the rowan staff, but with a much faster sped, provides much less damage add from the rain of XXX realm abilities.<br><br>---------------------------------------------------------------<br><br>2&gt;  The following log shows that the Rain of XXX are not stackable with each other, but ARE stackable with warden damage chants and enchanter damage add/damage shield:  Note that warden damage chant does not stack with enchanter damage add.<br><br>---------------------------------------------------------------<br><br>2a&gt;  Rain of Fire stacks with warden damage chant